#: includes/admin/class-admin-settings.php:974
msgid ""
"How long until cache files are automatically discarded. Expired caches are "
"regenerated on the next visit and cleaned up hourly by WP-Cron. Set to 0 for "
"unlimited — caches then persist until invalidated by an enabled Auto Purge "
"trigger (Auto Purge tab) or a manual \"Clear Cache\". For frequently updated "
"news sites, use 1-6 hours. For less active sites, use 1-7 days or unlimited. "
"Note: When .htaccess Optimization is enabled, Apache serves cached files "
"directly and cannot check file age. Expired files may continue to be served "
"until the next WP-Cron cleanup (runs hourly). If WP-Cron is disabled "
"(DISABLE_WP_CRON) and no system cron is configured to run wp-cron.php, the "
"cleanup will not run and expired files will keep being served indefinitely."
msgstr ""

